external_knowledge:
- 'lanterns of communication' metaphorically refers to wireless network standards;
- 'lit and updated beyond the dawn of 2022' implies standards updated after '2022-01-01';
- 'shine with an average glow' is a metaphor for having an average throughput;
- 'smallest shadow cast indoors' refers to the minimum indoor range of the standards.

sql:
SELECT standard_name, max_bandwidth
FROM wireless_standards
WHERE max_bandwidth > 54;

external_knowledge:
- '802.11a' refers to a wireless network standard that operates in the 5GHz frequency band;
- The indoor reach or range indicates the typical distance within which devices can communicate effectively under normal conditions;
- Typical throughput is a measure indicating how much data can be transferred in a network per second.

sql:
SELECT AVG(range_indoor) AS average_indoor_range
FROM wireless_standards
WHERE standard_status = 'active' AND security_features = 'WPA2';

SELECT standard_name 
FROM wireless_standards 
WHERE typical_throughput > (SELECT AVG(typical_throughput) FROM wireless_standards);

SELECT version_number, release_date
FROM standard_versions
WHERE standard_id = 3;

external_knowledge:
- 'shining stars of performance' refers to the top performance metrics;
- 'wireless galaxy' metaphorically represents the frequency bands;
- 'luminous metrics' represents the performance metrics with the highest values;
- The 'sky of each frequency band' metaphorically represents the scope of each frequency band.

sql:
SELECT standard_name 
FROM wireless_standards 
WHERE standard_id = 2;

SELECT ws.standard_name, fb.band_name
FROM wireless_standards ws
JOIN frequency_bands fb ON ws.frequency = fb.band_id;

SELECT MIN(typical_throughput)
FROM wireless_standards
WHERE standard_id = 0 AND range_indoor > 20;
